Syria Reopens Passage to Jordan Closed by Unrest, Petra Says

-- B y   N a y l a   R a z z o u k
-- 
2011-06-15T16:04:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/syria-reopens-passage-to-jordan-closed-by-unrest-petra-says.html
Syria  reopened the border post with
Jordan near the Syrian city of Daraa today after a two-month
closure due to the unrest in the country, the official Jordanian
 news agency ,  Petra , said.  The border post is open for 12 hours starting at 6 a.m.
local time, Petra said. Jordanian citizens may not be allowed
past the Daraa customs post into Syria “to ensure their safety,”
the news agency said, citing unidentified Syrian security
officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nayla Razzouk in Amman at 
 nrazzouk2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 